### **Architecture Specification (v4.2)**

# Bridge IDE: The "Lunar Elevator"

## **1. Core Identity & Philosophy**

**Bridge** is a **local-first, visual-first IDE** specialized for building **drift-proof UI components**.

- **Primary Output:** Framework-agnostic, single-file HTML "Blobs" for Google Sites (embed compatible).
    
- **Secondary Output:** Standard Multi-File Repositories (React, Vue, Svelte).
    
- **Core Philosophy:** "Mithril Clad" — the system actively prevents hallucinations and design drift through **rigid constraints**, while enabling a "Draft & Commit" workflow for rapid iteration.
    
- **Primary User:** Design Systems Leads & UX Designers who need to enforce consistency without sacrificing velocity.
    

---

## **2. System Architecture: "The Secure Hybrid"**

|**Layer**|**Technology**|**Role**|
|---|---|---|
|**App Shell**|**Electron (v29+)**|Native OS access (File System, Clipboard). Context isolation strictly enforced.|
|**UI Framework**|**React 18 + Tailwind**|Bridge's own interface (Shadcn UI components).|
|**Canvas Engine**|**`@xyflow/react` v12**|Infinite whiteboard for visual node manipulation.|
|**Data Core**|**SQLite (`better-sqlite3`)**|Local DB — project state, tokens, mappings, **overrides**, assets.|
|**Knowledge Base**|**`sqlite-vec`**|Local vector embeddings for Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG).|
|**AI Runtime**|**Anthropic SDK (Claude 3.7)**|Code generation and refactoring.|
|**Live Preview Engine**|**Iframe + Babel IPC**|Custom `srcdoc` iframe with local Babel compilation. 100% offline capable. Zero external dependencies. Replaced Sandpack to comply with strict CSP.|
|**AST Factory**|**Babel / Vue / Svelte ASTs**|Universal parsing engine to support multi-stack bi-directional edits.|
|**State**|**Zustand**|`canvasStore.ts` for React Flow and IDE state management.|
|**Validation**|**Zod**|Enforces schemas on all data nodes.|
|**Bundling**|**ESBuild WASM**|Blob Adapter — bundles to a single string client-side.|

